# Uptime Kuma - Self-Hosted Monitoring Tool

Uptime Kuma is an easy-to-use, self-hosted monitoring solution designed for tracking the availability and performance of various services and applications. Built with Node.js, Express, Socket.io, and Vue.js, it provides real-time monitoring capabilities with a modern, reactive web interface. The system supports monitoring HTTP/HTTPS endpoints, TCP ports, DNS records, ping checks, Docker containers, game servers, and more, with 20-second check intervals and comprehensive notification support.

The application architecture combines REST APIs for public-facing features like status badges and push notifications, with WebSocket APIs for real-time communication between the server and authenticated clients. It uses SQLite as the default database (with PostgreSQL, MySQL, and MariaDB support), and implements a modular notification system supporting 90+ services including Discord, Slack, Telegram, PagerDuty, and email. Key features include multi-language support, public status pages with custom domains, SSL certificate monitoring, maintenance window scheduling, 2FA authentication, and Prometheus metrics export.

## REST API Endpoints

### Push Monitor Heartbeat

```bash
# Push a heartbeat status from external systems (both GET and POST supported)
# Status "up" example
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/push/abc123token?status=up&msg=All%20systems%20operational&ping=45.2"

# Status "down" example
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/push/abc123token?status=down&msg=Service%20unavailable"

# Response
{
  "ok": true
}

# Error response
{
  "ok": false,
  "msg": "Monitor not found or not active."
}
```

### Generate Status Badge

```bash
# Get SVG badge showing current monitor status
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/status?label=Website&upColor=green&downColor=red&style=flat"

# With custom labels for each state
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/status?upLabel=Online&downLabel=Offline&pendingLabel=Starting&style=flat-square"

# Returns SVG badge image
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="90" height="20">...</svg>
```

### Generate Uptime Badge

```bash
# Get uptime percentage badge for last 24 hours (default)
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/uptime"

# Get uptime for last 7 days
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/uptime/720?label=Uptime&suffix=%&style=flat"

# Returns SVG badge with uptime percentage
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="110" height="20">...</svg>
```

### Generate Response Time Badge

```bash
# Get average response time badge for last 24 hours
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/avg-response?label=Response%20Time&suffix=ms"

# Get response time for custom duration
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/avg-response/168?label=Avg%20Response&color=blue"

# Returns SVG badge with average response time
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="140" height="20">...</svg>
```

### Generate Certificate Expiry Badge

```bash
# Get SSL certificate expiration badge
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/cert-exp?label=SSL%20Cert&warnDays=30&downDays=7"

# Custom colors for different states
curl "http://localhost:3001/api/badge/1/cert-exp?upColor=brightgreen&warnColor=yellow&downColor=red"

# Returns SVG badge showing days until certificate expiration
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="120" height="20">...</svg>
```

